stylometry: RISKSIMTABLE allows you to take multiple values and apply each of them as the input for a simulation and it will give you the results of each one of the quantities that you used for the inputs. It is used in a simulation model to provide the simulation the quantites you want to test. An example of a simulation model is when you have dependent costs for say ordering quantities of textbooks and those costs depend on how many you order, how many are sold compared to demand, how many are left over, etc. The RISKSIMTABLE allows you to try different quantities to apply to all those dependent costs and gives you back results for each of them so that you can achieve the optimal results.
